This Python program implements a Hangman game where users guess a randomly selected word letter by letter.
It uses random selection, loops, conditions, and strings to track guesses and display the game result.
import random
words = ["python", "java", "apple", "tiger", "hello"]
word = random.choice(words)
guessed = ""
attempts = 6
print("Welcome to Hangman!")
while attempts > 0:
display = ""
for char in word:
if char in guessed:
display += char
else:
display += "_"
print("Word:", display)
if display == word:
print("You won!")
break
guess = input("Guess a letter: ")
if guess in word:
guessed += guess
else:
attempts -= 1
print("Wrong guess! Attempts left:", attempts)
if attempts == 0:
print("Game Over! Word was:", word) decries the code
